Victory isn't in the future. Victory is won all the time, every single day.⁣
⁣
In this season, it can be so easy to say things like, "I can't wait to go back to normal." Or, "When all this is over with..."⁣
⁣
But the truth is, God has us here for a reason. The war won't be won when this virus is safely suppressed. The war is won each and every day when we choose to put Him first. We win the war when we wake up with the same spirit of hope. It's a victory when we open our Bibles, when we choose to continue trusting.⁣
⁣
It's just like how fitness isn't linear. You don't win the game when you've hit the goal, but you're a victor every day for just showing up.⁣
⁣
Victory is won in the daily moments, in all-the-time choices and in prioritizing faith over fear.⁣
⁣
